I"n<p>Rain is a simple and clean <a href="https://jekyllrb.com/">Jekyll</a> theme with focus on content. This theme is heavily inspired by <a href="https://github.com/chesterhow/tale">Tale</a> theme.</p>

<h2 id="rain-features">Rain features</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Compatible with GitHub Pages</li>
  <li>Compatible with Netlify</li>
  <li>Responsive design</li>
  <li>Syntax highlighting, with the help of Pygments</li>
  <li>Markdown and HTML text formatting</li>
  <li>Pagination of posts</li>
  <li>Social media links with icons</li>
  <li>Related posts</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="browser-support">Browser Support</h2>
<p>Rain works on most if not all modern browsers, including Chrome, Safari and Firefox</p>

<h2 id="download-or-contribute">Download or Contribute</h2>
<p>Rain is publicly hosted on GitHub, so go ahead and download or fork it at the <a href="#">GitHub repository</a>.</p>
